questiontext.text:
Consider \(U_f: |x,y\rangle \to | x, y \oplus f(x)\rangle\) for a function \(f:\{0,1\} \to \{0,1\}\).

Give, if possible, the resulting state in ket notation. If the result depends on \(f\), write depends.

  • \(U_f (| 0 \rangle \otimes |+\rangle) = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]
  • \(U_f (| 0 \rangle \otimes |-\rangle) = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]
  • \(U_f (| - \rangle \otimes |+\rangle) = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]
  • \(U_f (| 0 \rangle \otimes |0\rangle) = \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]

Give the answer in ket-notation. Insert \(|000\rangle\) as ket(000) (that is correct, even though the preview will cut out leading 0s and show \(|0\rangle\) always), \(|100\rangle\) as ket(100), â€¦ .
